==English==

===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[قراءة]]}} (qirā’a, "reading", "recitation"), from {{ARchar|[[قرأ]]}} (qará’a, "to declaim", "to recite").

===Proper noun===
'''the Qur’an'''

# The [[Islamic]] holy book, considered to be God’s message for mankind as revealed to [[Muhammad]].
# A copy of this book.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Koran]]
*[[Alcoran]] (''obsolete'')

